## Plan

### Step 1: Replace hero headline and subhead in InstallHero

File: `src/components/LandingPage/InstallHero/index.tsx`

- [x] Replace the h1 text. The current headline is "AIDE collapses the
      specialist hire into the agent loop." — this is explicitly listed in
      the LP spec Bad Examples as a subtler failure mode. Replace it with
      one of the two spec-approved variants. The LP spec Good Examples
      section provides both verbatim:
      - Variant A: "Describe what you want. AIDE cascades your intent into
        working code."
      - Variant B: "Tell your agents what to build, not how to build it."
      The implementor picks one. Both are approved by the spec.
- [x] Replace the subhead paragraph. The current subhead reads "A research
      agent studies your domain, persists findings to your brain, and six
      specialized agents..." — this leads with the research agent rather
      than addressing both audiences. Replace with copy that names both
      entry points (non-technical users who describe outcomes, and technical
      builders who research unfamiliar domains) and mentions the six named
      agents and the persistent brain. Use the spec Good Examples subhead
      copy as the template (Variant A or B, matching whichever headline was
      chosen). The subhead must end with "Works with Claude Code today."

Spec trace: LP spec `outcomes.undesired` bullet 4 (copy that could be
pasted onto any agent framework); LP spec Bad Examples paragraph 3
(the "AIDE collapses the specialist hire" failure mode); LP spec
Good Examples hero copy variants A and B; LP spec Strategy "Hero leads
with cascading intent and accessibility."

