- [x] Ship only the universal anchor figure. The LP spec Good Examples
      provides the exact copy verbatim: "A six-month fractional specialist
      engagement runs $30,000-$60,000 at the low end (Geisheker Group,
      2026). AIDE captures the same domain knowledge for free via npx."
      Use this copy as-is. The strong tags should wrap "$30,000-$60,000"
      and the citation should be in a muted span, matching the existing
      styling pattern.
- [x] Change the section label from "What you replace" to a label that
      reflects the new framing. The LP spec Strategy names this beat
      "Cost-of-not-knowing strip" and the spec says it "anchors the
      business case: domain knowledge has historically been expensive to
      acquire." A label like "The cost of not knowing" or "What domain
      knowledge costs" fits. The implementor picks the exact wording; the
      constraint is that it must not reference replacing specialists or
      hiring.

Spec trace: LP spec Good Examples "Cost-of-not-knowing strip copy (ship
verbatim, cite inline)"; LP spec Strategy "Cost strip ships one anchor
